spans.text: crowded walls , whose well-enlightened round With lovers sighs and protestations sound , You pictures flattered by the learnt and wise , You glasses ogled by the brightest eyes
the first who paired The erring footman with the unerring card
of the gay and fair , From distant Bloomsbury to Grosvenor's square
inspires a sullen gloom , And brooding sadness fills the slighted room
If but some happier female's card
The crowded floors , which groan beneath their feet
Will sooth the tumults of my raging breast

The loathed ideas of the crowding guests
the discord of my restless mind
